---
title: Chilli and Cherry Tomato Orzo with parsley and grated Italian Cheese
description: This creamy veggie orzo is both filling and filled with flavour. Mushrooms, cherry tomatoes and fragrant garlic make this an abundant dish, with optional spice in the form of fresh chilli for the heat seekers out there.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/HF_Y23_R14_W29_IE_IEVCLV15600-2_Main_high-b9c10179.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipecards/card/6447ebcfdc62658e1c0cc4f6.pdf
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.ie/recipes/chilli-and-cherry-tomato-orzo-6447ebcfdc62658e1c0cc4f6
course: main course
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: Italian
nutrition:
  calories: 525 kcal
  fat: 17.2 g
  saturated fat: 10.6 g
  carbohydrates: 72.3 g
  sugar: 9.1 g
  protein: 21.8 g
  sodium: 2.7 g
  serving size: 347
servings: 2
---

Peel and grate the @garlic{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Quarter the @mushrooms{125%g}, halving any larger quarters.

Halve the @chilli{1} lengthways. Deseed and finely chop.

Roughly chop the @parsley{5%g} (stalks and all).

---

Place a large #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, fry the garlic, mushrooms and @cherry tomatoes{250%g} until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-6%minutes}.

---

Add the @Hello Muscat{1%sachet}, @water{400%ml}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and @butter{1%tbsp} (double all for 4p) to the pot.

Stir in half the parsley along with the @dried orzo{170%g} and chopped chilli (use less if you don't like spice).

Bring to the boil, cover and simmer until the orzo is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Stir every ~{3-4%minutes} to prevent sticking.

Stir through the @creme fraiche{65%g} and half the @grated Italian style hard cheese{50%g} then season to taste with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

---

Divide your creamy veggie orzo between #bowls{}.

Top with a scattering of the remaining parsley and grated cheese.